3. The Grand Bazaar

The Grand Bazaar is not where artifacts are created.

It’s where they become discoverable and combinable.

It’s like:
	•	a city market square
	•	the Linux package registry
	•	the npm ecosystem
	•	the arXiv of tools

It allows:
	•	cross-domain recombination
	•	unexpected discovery
	•	reputation formation
	•	emergent standards

The bazaar doesn’t replace local markets.

It links them.

⸻

4. The Marketplace Primitive

Here is the single primitive that makes the whole system work:

Artifact Cards

Every item in the marketplace must be represented by a standard card.

Think of them like:
	•	Pokémon cards
	•	Magic cards
	•	research abstracts
	•	package registry entries

A card is the atomic tradable object.

⸻

