6. Market Signals

Markets need signals that indicate usefulness.

Better signals than simple popularity:

Reuse Count

How often an artifact is used in other artifacts.

Adaptation Count

How often it is modified or extended.

Cross-Domain Portability

How many markets it appears in.

Constraint Survival

Whether its invariants remain intact after transformations.

These metrics measure structural usefulness, not hype.

